<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="884" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111N83/39</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SHFA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-03T19:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 4, 12.30
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1209. My telegram No. 1189, September 29, 5 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d884fn1">Not printed.</note> I am in receipt of a <hi rend="italic">note verbale</hi> from the Foreign Office dated today
                            reading as follows in translation from the French: <pb facs="0955" n="1789" xml:id="pg_1789"/>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The Ministry for Foreign Affairs has the honor to bring to the
                                    knowledge of the Legation of the United States of America that
                                    automatic [contact] mines will be placed by the Royal Norwegian
                                    Navy in the part of Norwegian territorial waters comprised
                                    between 59° 8′ and 59° 25′ north latitude and [west] of 5° 10′
                                    longitude east of Greenwich. For this reason the above indicated
                                    areas will be closed to ordinary traffic from Monday, October 7,
                                    1918.</p>
                                <p>The Legation of Norway at Washington has been instructed to bring
                                    the foregoing to the knowledge of the Government of the United
                                    States of America.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SHFA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>